a, Hon. Felix Uba, High Chief Johnbosco Onunkwo among others.<img class="size-full wp-image-1518063 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?resize=600%2C398&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="398" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?resize=300%2C199&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?resize=58%2C38&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?resize=260%2C172&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?resize=196%2C130&amp;ssl=1 196w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/chieftains.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> During the meeting, stakeholders of the party brainstormed the way forward for the South East zone, especially in the All Progressive Congress, believing that winning the Anambra Gubernatorial election coming up in 2021 will make the party stronger in the zone. Vanguard News Nigeria THE All Progressives Congress, APC, stakeholders in Imo State are holding discussions with the governorship candidate of the Peoples Democrstic Party, PDP, Chief Emeka Ihedioha, with the aim of supporting the party if Senator Hope Uzodinma fails to clinche the governorship ticket of the party for 2019. October 12, 2018 In "News" By Ugochukwu Alaribe A chieftain of the All Progressive Grand Alliance, APGA, in Abia State, Prince Nnanna Ukaegbu, has warned that the party risks not fielding candidates for the 2021 Anambra governorship and the 2023 general elections if the stakeholders of the party fail to rescue APGA from what he… June 3, 2019 In "News" Apex Igbo socio-cultural organisation, Ohanaeze Ndigbo and billi